full_content.content: Common reasons your Samsung dryer display is not working
The most common reasons your Samsung dryer display is not working are a defective electronic control board, defective power supply board or an inoperative user interface control.
We can help! Our service technicians have repaired over
Samsung dryers. We can fix yours no matter where you bought it.
Most common repairs needed to fix a Samsung dryer

When your dryer display is not working, a defective electronic control board could be preventing the control panel from powering up. Wires connect the user interface control board in the control panel to the electronic control board inside the dryer. When a defective electronic control board fails to send power and proper signals to the user interface control and control panel, the dryer won’t turn on. When your dryer is completely dead, have a Sears Home Services Technician visit your home and fix the problem.
How to replace the electronic control board in an electric dryer

When the display is not working on your dryer, a defective power supply board may need replacing. The power supply board distributes electrical current from the dryer power cord to the electronic control board and other components in the dryer. When the power supply board doesn’t send power to the electronic control board or the control panel, the dryer won’t power up. When your dryer is completely dead, have a Sears Home Services Technician visit your home and check the dryer. The technician will replace the power supply board if it’s defective.

When the dryer control panel display is not working, an inoperative user interface control could be causing the failure. The user interface control sends power and signals to the control panel to operate the display and indicator lights. When the control panel is completely dead, have a Sears Home Services Repair Expert visit your home and check the dryer. The technician will replace the user interface control if it’s defective.
What are the common parts of a dryer?
Why is my dryer display not working?

Power issues with your Samsung dryer can stem from your home’s power supply. A bad power cord, wiring failure or defective electronic control board in the dryer can also prevent the dryer from powering up.

full_content.content: Follow these basic troubleshooting steps to check the power supply going to your dryer:
Make sure that the dryer power cord is properly plugged in.
Reset the house circuit breaker for the dryer to make sure the outlet is getting power.

For a gas dryer, plug a night light or small appliance into the electrical outlet for the dryer to test for power. If the item doesn’t get power from the outlet, have an electrician repair the electrical outlet in your home.
Examine the power cord and its wiring connections
and check the power cord for damage. Replace the power cord if it’s damaged.
For an electric dryer, check the power cord wire connections on the terminal block at the back of the dryer
. The image above shows how the power cord wires should be connected on an electric dryer.
Reconnect any loose power cord wires.
check the wiring connection on the main electronic control board. Reconnect any loose wires.
If you see damage to the control board such as burn spots, you’ll likely need to replace the main control board.
Here’s a safe DIY video that shows how to replace the main electronic control board on a common type of dryer:
If you’re not completely confident that you can repair the dryer on your own, schedule
service and we’ll send a Sears Home Services technician to your home to fix the problem.
What to expect when you experience a Samsung dryer display not working issue
How is the display not working problem fixed?

Correcting most display not working problems usually involves replacing the electronic control board, power supply board or user interface control. However, there are many potential causes, so a thorough diagnosis is key to fixing the problem. An accurate diagnosis is essential to understanding how much the repair will be.
Sears Home Services recommendations for a dryer display that is not working

When the dryer display is not working it can be for many reasons. To avoid replacing unneeded parts we recommend having a Sears Home Services professional perform diagnostic tests to identify the root cause of the problem. Our technicians are experienced at diagnosing all types of dryer failures.
What to look out for with a dryer display not working diagnosis

Diagnosing modern appliances without proper knowledge and training can be difficult. Without using proper diagnostic techniques, fixing your dryer problem will only be achieved through changing parts on a hunch. Appliances, especially in the last 10 years, have become extremely advanced, and many models have electronic parts that are difficult to test. DIY repairs on the latest appliance models are becoming increasingly difficult.
No visual on a Samsung dryer’s panel makes cycle selection guesswork. Loose wires or a damaged control board frequently cause this. If restarts fail, opt for
. Skilled repairs restore an active display so you can monitor each load effectively.

full_content.content: Why is the display on my Samsung dryer not working?
Check if the dryer is receiving power, and inspect the control board for any malfunction or loose wire harness connections.
Could a faulty control board cause the display to stop working?
Yes, a malfunctioning control board may cause the display not to function. Replacing the control board could solve the issue.
How do I fix the display on my Samsung dryer?
Ensure the dryer is plugged in and check the wiring connections. If the control board is damaged, replace it.
What causes a dryer’s display to stop working?
Issues with the power supply, control board failure, or disconnected wires could prevent the display from working properly.

full_content.content: Deciphering Samsung Clothes Dryer Error Codes
Find the most common Samsung clothes dryer error codes and their solutions. Get professional help from Sears Home Services.
A dryer drum is the main interior component of a clothes dryer where clothes are placed to be dried. It rotates during the drying cycle, allowing heated air to circulate through the clothes.

A dryer filter, commonly known as a lint filter, is a component of a clothes dryer that captures lint and other debris from clothes during the drying process, preventing them from clogging the dryer vent.
A dryer pedestal is a platform that elevates a dryer off the ground, making it easier to load and unload laundry while also providing additional storage space in some models.

A dryer rack is an accessory for clothes dryers that provides a stationary platform to dry items without tumbling, ideal for delicate or bulky items, or shoes that might be damaged by the usual drying cycle.
Additional possible Samsung dryer symptoms you may experience
Samsung dryer makes noise when tumbling
Samsung dryer sensor dry not working
Samsung dryer taking a long time to dry
These dryer brands may also experience display not working
